Badlands is winter - isolated and cold, cynical about the world. It is also a time for self reflecting, turning within yourself. Winter is often used to symbolize painful experiences in life - but it also heralds the return of spring.

IICHLIWP is fall, it’s adulthood and a life full of the bounty of the harvest season, but it also looks towards the distant future - the future of your family without you. Fall is the peak of the harvest, and abundance but also the start of decay - looking towards the winter.

HFK is summer. Full of lonely, empty stretches of time glimmering in the heat; filling your time with meaningless flings. Summer is youthful ignorance, feeling naively powerful in the face of the world.

Elaboration: Manic is spring. It’s a rebirth, the return of joy. The first bright flower petals blooming in a barren landscape. It is a season of new beginnings, of looking to the future, while mourning what didn’t make it through the winter. Planting seeds for the future.
